    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "1fbcd038c446adb2",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "1fbcd038c446adb2",
        "text": "**The storytelling quadrant** \nruns from \n- undisciplined gossip, where rigour is minimal and highly informal, resting in ‘trust’ and senses of ‘authenticity’ or a loose sense and emotionally manipulable of plausibility; through\n- skilled storytelling - for example, by bards or griots - within traditions of literary, historical, mythological or folk genre, into \n- journalism (news from elsewhere) of more and less rigorous kinds; into \n- historical and strategic narrative (also news from elsewhere) founded in firm conceptualisations rather than rhetorical flows whose terms skip from one meaning to another in a button-pushing play of memes."
      },
      "date": 1609415411370
    },
    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "1fbcd038c446adb2",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "1fbcd038c446adb2",
        "text": "**The storytelling quadrant** \nruns from \n- undisciplined gossip, where rigour is minimal and highly informal, resting in ‘trust’ and senses of ‘authenticity’ or a loose sense and emotionally manipulable of plausibility; through\n- skilled storytelling - for example, by bards or griots - within traditions of literary, historical, mythological or folk genre. Also, novels or short fiction; into \n- journalism (news from elsewhere) of more and less rigorous kinds; into \n- insightful dramatic composition and skilful drama production, on one hand, and, on the other\n- poetry; and ultimately, into\n- historical and strategic narrative (also news from elsewhere) founded in firm conceptualisations rather than rhetorical flows whose terms skip from one meaning to another in a button-pushing play of memes."
      },
      "date": 1609415619397
